a championship team. Finally, we seek people with the desire and capacity to build and share expertise in the frontier technologies of crypto and blockchain, in whatever way is most relevant to their role. Read more about our values and culture here. Cloud: Infrastructure is not a back office function at Coinbase. It is a product that we hold to the same quality standards as any other that we ship externally. We\u2019ve built some of the most secure infrastructure running in the public cloud and consider automation and tooling a competitive advantage for the company. Developer Productivity: The Developer Productivity team helps Coinbase engineers realize this vision by enabling them to design, develop and deploy software quickly, reliably and securely. We consider the engineering teams as our customers and work closely with them throughout our development process. Reliability: The Reliability Engineering team helps Coinbase realize its vision by supporting engineering teams to build software that is world-class in terms of its reliability. As a core service team, the Coinbase Reliability Engineers work closely with the rest of engineering. We proactively seek out and gather the state-of-the-art, best practices from the industry at large. What we look for in you: At least 7+ years software engineering experience in industry You exhibit our core values: clear communication, positive energy, continuous learning, and efficient execution You know what high quality code \u2014 and software engineering processes \u2014 look like and know how to foster an environment that creates them You showcase solid working proficiency within a modern tech stack. We typically use a mix of Ruby, Go and JavaScript for languages and gRPC + Protobuf for communication. Use these before? Great. If not, that\u2019s okay too. Our focus is hiring smart engineers who\u2019ve worked on complex problems and we trust you\u2019ll be able to pick up new tech on the job You have built systems on public cloud providers such as AWS, GCP or Azure Curious to learn more? Apply and check out these links: Monitorama PDX 2019 - Luke Demi - Logs, Metrics, and the Evolution of Observability at Coinbase: link AWS re:Invent 2019: How Coinbase handles incident management by leveraging AWS: link Nine Serverless Patterns: Intro to Lambda for Startups: link Coinbase is committed to diversity in its workforce and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and to review all of our job postings to minimize biased language. Coinbase does not make hiring or employment decisions on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, gender, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy, sex, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, citizenship, or any other basis protected by applicable local, state or federal law. Coinbase will also consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records in a manner consistent with San Francisco\u2019s Fair Chance Ordinance and similar local laws. Global Data Privacy Notice for Job Candidates and Applicants Depending on your location, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) may regulate the way we manage the data of job applicants. Our full notice outlining how your data will be processed as part of the application procedure for application locations is available here: Ireland/EU, United Kingdom, and California. By submitting your application, you are agreeing to our use and processing of your data as required. Show full job description Apply Now Stay Connected Contact Us SimplyHired Blog Facebook Twitter LinkedIn YouTube Job Tools Local Jobs Salary Estimator Post Jobs Free Resume Builder Browse All Jobs All Salaries All Cities All Companies Guides Resumes Cover Letters Interviews Careers Take your job search wherever you go. United States United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlan